dministrators     Help     Sandbox     Recent Changes                          in: International Confederation of Wizards members, Males, Swiss individuals, Wizards         English     Deutsch   Deutsch   Español   Français   Polski   Português do Brasil   Русский   中文               Heinrich Eberstadt              View source                         History                         Talk (0)                                         Heinrich Eberstadt   Biographical information  Nationality Swiss[1]    Physical information  Species Human[1]   Gender Male[1]    Affiliation  Occupation Swiss delegate of the International Confederation of Wizards[1]   Loyalty International Confederation of Wizards[1]   [Source]    "Our American friends have permitted a breach of the Statue of Secrecy that threatens to expose us all." — Heinrich Eberstadt addressing the Pentagram meeting[src]  Heinrich Eberstadt was a Swiss wizard who was a delegate of the International Confederation of Wizards.[1]  Contents  1 Biography 2 Behind the scenes 3 Appearances 4 Notes and references   Biography On 6 December 1926, he attended an emergency meeting of the International Confederation of Wizards to discuss magical disturbances in New York, including the No-Maj Senator Henry Shaw Junior.[1] President of the Magical Congress of the United States of America, Seraphina Picquery, rebuked his criticisms, noting that she would not be lectured by the man who let Gellert Grindelwald slip through his fingers.[1]  Behind the scenes Heinrich Eberstadt is portrayed by Martin Oelbermann in the film inspired by Fantastic Beasts and Where to Find Them.[2] Appearances Fantastic Beasts and Where to Find Them: The Original Screenplay (First appearance) Fantastic Beasts and Where to Find Them (film) Notes and references   ↑ 1.0 1.1 1.2 1.3 1.4 1.5 1.6 1.7 Fantastic Beasts and Where to Find Them: The Original Screenplay, Scene 60  ↑  Martin Oelbermann at the Internet Movie Database     International Confederation of Wiza